  <!-- HERO -->
  <h1>Manhattan Commercial Security Gap Scorecard <span style="font-size:16px;color:var(--muted)">(3-min self-audit)</span></h1>
  <p class="muted">Find the 5 hidden gaps causing after-hours breaches, visitor leaks, and slow emergency response—then get the exact steps to fix them fast.</p>
  <p class="muted" style="font-size:13px">Built specifically for Manhattan office, mixed-use, and commercial properties.</p>

  <div class="hr"></div>

  <!-- HOW TO + VISUAL SCORE BANDS -->
  <h2>How to use this scorecard</h2>
  <ol class="muted" style="margin:0 0 12px 20px">
    <li>Mark <strong>Yes</strong> or <strong>No</strong> for each check.</li>
    <li>Score <strong>1 point per “Yes”</strong>. Max 10.</li>
    <li>Review each question below and apply the matching fixes.</li>
  </ol>
  <div class="scorebands">
    <div class="crit"><strong style="color:var(--red)">0–3 Critical Risk</strong><br><span class="muted">Multiple after-hours exposures likely. Fix within 48 hours.</span></div>
    <div class="mod"><strong style="color:#a16207">4–7 Moderate</strong><br><span class="muted">Core controls exist, but gaps remain. Prioritize failed checks.</span></div>
    <div class="strong"><strong style="color:var(--emerald)">8–10 Strong</strong><br><span class="muted">Solid fundamentals. Maintain cadence and tighten exceptions.</span></div>
  </div>

  <div class="hr"></div>

  <!-- PROOF / AUTHORITY (non-numerical to avoid claims; swap with a sourced stat if you want) -->
  <h2>Local context that matters</h2>
  <p class="muted" style="margin-top:4px">
    After 6 PM is when most exposures surface in hybrid buildings—elevators bypass lobbies, contractors arrive, and monitoring is thinnest.
  </p>

  <div class="hr"></div>

  <!-- THE 10 CHECKS with ICONS + GAP→PROTOCOL MAPPING -->
  <h2>The 10 Yes/No Checks (grouped by 5 gaps)</h2>

  <!-- 1) After-Hours Access -->
  <div class="gap">
    <div class="gap-head"><svg><use href="#i-lock"/></svg><h3>After-Hours Access Control</h3></div>
    <ul>
      <li>☐ Are elevator/floor restrictions automatically enforced after 6 PM (card or PIN), including freight/service?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>Elevator Access Configuration Checklist</em></span>
      </li>
      <li>☐ Have you completed a Monthly Access Audit in the last 30 days and revoked all stale credentials?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>Monthly Access Audit Template</em></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- 2) Visitor Management -->
  <div class="gap" style="margin-top:12px">
    <div class="gap-head"><svg><use href="#i-badge"/></svg><h3>Visitor Management</h3></div>
    <ul>
      <li>☐ Is pre-registration required after 6 PM with government ID capture and host approval prior to entry?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>After-Hours Visitor SOP</em></span>
      </li>
      <li>☐ Are visitor egress logs matched to ingress every day (no unclosed visits after-hours)?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>Visitor Lifecycle Reconciliation Log</em></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- 3) Tech + Human Oversight -->
  <div class="gap" style="margin-top:12px">
    <div class="gap-head"><svg><use href="#i-camera"/></svg><h3>Tech + Human Oversight</h3></div>
    <ul>
      <li>☐ Do all entry/egress points have camera coverage with &gt;30 days retention and live monitoring after 6 PM?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>Camera Coverage QA Checklist</em> + <em>Live Monitoring Playbook</em></span>
      </li>
      <li>☐ Are exception reports (forced/held-open doors, tailgating alerts) auto-generated and reviewed each shift?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>Exception Analytics Runbook</em></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- 4) Emergency Coordination -->
  <div class="gap" style="margin-top:12px">
    <div class="gap-head"><svg><use href="#i-siren"/></svg><h3>Emergency Coordination</h3></div>
    <ul>
      <li>☐ Is a current (≤90 days) Contact Tree maintained with primary + backup contacts (PM lead, vendor, FDNY/NYPD, tenant reps)?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>Emergency Contact Tree</em></span>
      </li>
      <li>☐ Have you run a micro-drill in the last 60 days (fire, medical, intrusion) with documented lessons learned?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>Micro-Drill Cadence + Tracker</em></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- 5) Guard Coverage & Training -->
  <div class="gap" style="margin-top:12px">
    <div class="gap-head"><svg><use href="#i-guard"/></svg><h3>Guard Coverage &amp; Training</h3></div>
    <ul>
      <li>☐ Is there a written backup coverage policy guaranteeing ≥2 guards after 6 PM with clear escalation paths?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>Backup Coverage Policy Rubric</em></span>
      </li>
      <li>☐ Have all guards been briefed this quarter on the After-Hours Escort SOP with sign-off and spot checks?
        <span class="map"><b>If NO ⇒</b> Fix with: <em>After-Hours Escort SOP</em></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="hr"></div>

<!-- 48-Hour Gap Plug Plan — Exact Protocols (Expanded) -->
<h2>48-Hour Gap Plug Plan — Exact Protocols</h2>

<style>
  /* small add-ons for richer layout (scoped to .msg-authority) */
  .msg-authority .proto-grid{display:grid;gap:12px}
  .msg-authority .proto-card{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;padding:14px;background:#fff}
  .msg-authority .proto-head{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:6px}
  .msg-authority .proto-head svg{width:22px;height:22px;color:#0b1220}
  .msg-authority .meta{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:6px 0 8px}
  .msg-authority .meta .tag{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:999px;padding:4px 10px;font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);background:#f8fafc}
  .msg-authority .label{font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:6px}
  .msg-authority .steps{margin:6px 0 0 20px}
  .msg-authority .why{background:#f8fafc;border:1px dashed var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:10px;margin-top:10px;color:var(--muted);font-size:14px}
</style>

<div class="proto-grid">

  <!-- Monthly Access Audit Template -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-lock"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Monthly Access Audit Template</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Property Manager + Security Supervisor</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Day 1 export → Day 2 revoke & file</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Signed audit log + revocation report</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps (do this within 48 hours):</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Export 30-day badgeholder & door activity from ACS + visitor system.</li>
      <li>Cross-match with HR roster & vendor contracts; flag inactive/expired/unknown.</li>
      <li>Immediately suspend stale credentials; notify tenant admins.</li>
      <li>Issue a “Cards Reviewed / Revoked / Exceptions” report; PM signs off and files.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why (Manhattan):</strong> Stale contractor cards are a common after-hours breach path in mixed-use towers; revocations close the fastest risk.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- Elevator Access Configuration Checklist -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-lock"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Elevator Access Configuration Checklist</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Access Control Vendor Tech</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Within 24 hours of finding the gap</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Schedule screenshots + pass/fail test log</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Inventory all cabs (incl. freight/service) and restricted floors after 18:00.</li>
      <li>Program controller schedules to deny non-authorized floors 18:00–06:00.</li>
      <li>Test 3 random tenant cards + 1 vendor card after 20:00 on each cab.</li>
      <li>Align lobby & freight rules; attach screenshots to the change record.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Elevators bypass lobby screening; after-hours floor locks stop tailgating at the source.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- After-Hours Visitor SOP -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-badge"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">After-Hours Visitor SOP</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Lobby Guard + PM Oversight</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Distribute same day; brief next shift</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> SOP card posted; supervisor sign-off</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Require host pre-approval in VMS after 18:00; deny walk-ins.</li>
      <li>Scan gov ID; match to pre-reg; log visitor photo where legal.</li>
      <li>Issue time-boxed access; escort vendors per SOP; log exit at egress.</li>
      <li>Nightly reconcile open visits; escalate mismatches to PM.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Most “quiet” violations are unclosed visits; strict lifecycle control kills that risk.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- Visitor Lifecycle Reconciliation Log -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-badge"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Visitor Lifecycle Reconciliation Log</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Night Shift Supervisor</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Daily 07:00 handover</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Signed reconciliation sheet</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Pull “after-hours visitor” report for prior night.</li>
      <li>Compare entries vs. exits; list all open visits.</li>
      <li>Contact hosts; close or escalate outstanding records within 24h.</li>
      <li>Log root-causes (host missed, badge issue, SOP gap) and corrective action.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Open visits create liability and mask tailgating; a daily closeout is a Manhattan must-do.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- Camera Coverage QA Checklist -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-camera"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Camera Coverage QA Checklist</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Guard Supervisor + Camera Vendor</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Night walk within 48h</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> QA sheet + screenshots + work orders</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Night-walk all ingress/egress, docks, garages, roof access; verify angles & illumination.</li>
      <li>Check NVR retention (goal ≥30 days; align with policy/regulations).</li>
      <li>Capture “before” screenshots; open tickets for blind spots/failures.</li>
      <li>Retest and attach “after” evidence once fixed.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Clear night footage speeds incident resolution; blind spots are exploited after 6 PM.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- Exception Analytics Runbook -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-camera"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Exception Analytics Runbook</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Security IT / ACS Admin</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Enable within 24h; review every shift</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Shift report with incidents & actions</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Enable alerts for forced/held-open doors and tailgating in ACS/VMS.</li>
      <li>Schedule email reports to the shift inbox at 06:00 & 18:00.</li>
      <li>Supervisors review, open tickets for repeats, and log actions.</li>
      <li>Weekly trend review with PM; escalate chronic problem doors.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Analytics surface silent failures (stuck magnets, propped doors) that guards miss on rounds.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- Live Monitoring Playbook -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-camera"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Live Monitoring Playbook (After 18:00)</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Guard Shift Supervisor</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Roll out next after-hours shift</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Hourly initials on monitoring checklist</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Assign posts to specific feeds (entry/egress, freight, roof access).</li>
      <li>Define 2-minute screen scan cadence; prioritize exception alerts.</li>
      <li>Escalate incidents within 3 minutes to supervisor + PM.</li>
      <li>Log events with clip references (timestamp/channel).</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Human confirmation + crisp escalation beat automated alerts alone in Manhattan’s mixed-use patterns.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- Emergency Contact Tree -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-siren"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Emergency Contact Tree</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> PM Admin</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Verify & redistribute within 48h</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Call-down log + laminated copies</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Collect primary + backup numbers for PM, vendor, FDNY/NYPD liaison, tenant safety reps.</li>
      <li>Live-call each number to verify; note answer/voicemail/time.</li>
      <li>Print laminated copies for lobby & command post; store digital master in shared drive.</li>
      <li>Set 90-day reminder to re-verify.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Failed numbers add minutes to response; verified backups keep momentum during incidents.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- Micro-Drill Cadence + Tracker -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-siren"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Micro-Drill Cadence + Tracker</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Guard Supervisor + PM Lead</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Run first drill within 48h; schedule monthly</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Drill log with timing & actions</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Pick scenario (fire/medical/intrusion) most relevant to your tenants.</li>
      <li>Run 15-minute drill; time response to first action & full resolution.</li>
      <li>Document friction points; assign owners & due dates.</li>
      <li>Share outcomes with tenants’ life-safety reps if applicable.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Frequent, small reps harden muscle memory; you fix real bottlenecks, not imaginary ones.</div>
  </article>

  <!-- Backup Coverage Policy Rubric -->
  <article class="proto-card">
    <div class="proto-head"><svg><use href="#i-guard"/></svg><h3 style="margin:0">Backup Coverage Policy Rubric</h3></div>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="tag"><strong>Owner:</strong> Security Vendor Manager</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Draft policy in 48h; brief next shift</span>
      <span class="tag"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Signed policy + guard acknowledgements</span>
    </div>
    <div class="label">Steps:</div>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Set a minimum 2-guard after-hours standard; define float coverage for breaks.</li>
      <li>Maintain on-call roster with ≤30-minute arrival SLA; test monthly.</li>
      <li>Run a quarterly surge stress test (e.g., fire alarm during VIP event).</li>
      <li>Collect guard acknowledgements; store in personnel files.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="why"><strong>Why:</strong> Incidents escalate when only one guard is on duty; redundancy + practiced handoffs prevent gaps.</div>
  </article>

</div>


